Cholera broke out in Yemen on 27 April and has seen at least 789 deaths. GENEVA - The number of suspected cholera cases in Yemen has risen to more than 100,000 since an outbreak began on 27 April, the World Health Organization (WHO) said on Thursday.&quot;To date, 101,820 suspected cholera cases and 789 deaths have been reported in 19 governorates,&quot; WHO spokesman Tarik Jasarevic said.